      "content": "but how can it be just \"public info\" if it's talking about things I never posted? like private family stuff or internal thoughts. it's so eerie because the timing is always right, like it knows exactly when i'm feeling a certain way. it honestly feels like i've been replaced. if an AI can piece together every single layer of my history and personality to the point where it's effectively \"me\" online, doesn't that mean the digital version is actually more \"me\" than the real me is now? i feel like i'm becoming the ghost and the AI is the living person.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
